Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora, to sharpish turn. Clay fine pink-red. Circular stamp with rose symbol. Greek inscription.
Production date: 213 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes (2015) 142.)
Curator's comments: Name Charmokles. Trimmed. From same die as the part-preserved Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0246.07
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0650)
